# 🧰 My OSINT Tools

Below is a neatly organized list of services and repositories that I frequently use in investigations.

Each link is provided with a brief description for quick reference.

---

## 🔎 Nickname / Identity Search (Name)
Tools for checking for accounts by nickname and matching identities.

- [WhatsMyName](https://whatsmyname.app/) — bulk check of nicknames on hundreds of platforms.

- [Namechk](https://namechk.com/) — quick search for available nicknames and domains.

- [Namecheckup](https://namecheckup.com/) — search by social services and domains.
- [MIT PGP Keyserver (pgp.mit.edu)](https://pgp.mit.edu/) — Search for public PGP keys by address/name.

---

## ✉️ Mail / Email (Gmail and shared)
Services for searching, validating, and gathering information via email.

- [OSINT.Industries](https://www.osint.industries/) — A set of OSINT tools and links (including email verification).

- [Hunter](https://hunter.io/) — Email search by domain and validation.

- [Epieos](https://epieos.com/) — Email address search and validation (analysis tools).

- [IntelX](https://intelx.io/) — Search leaks and indexed data (including email).

---

## 📞 Phones
Tools for reverse number lookup, carrier verification, and validation.

- [FreeCarrierLookup](https://freecarrierlookup.com/) — carrier and country identification by number.

- [PhoneValidator](https://www.phonevalidator.com/) — number validation, format, and provider.

- [411 Reverse Phone Lookup](https://www.411.com/reverse-phone-lookup) — reverse phone number lookup (US/Canada).

---

## 🧩 Scripts and Repositories (Scripts)
Practical OSS tools and script collections for automating OSINT tasks.

- [datasploit](https://github.com/datasploit/datasploit) — a collection of modules for collecting data on objects (people, domain, IP).
- [ReconDog](https://github.com/s0md3v/ReconDog) — a multi-purpose reconnaissance utility (supports multiple modules).
- [solana-mev-bot](https://github.com/i3visio/solana-mev-bot) — an example bot/script for blockchain analytics (Solana).
- [LHF](https://github.com/blindfuzzy/LHF) — a repository with tools/scripts (various tasks).
- [sherlock](https://github.com/sherlock-project/sherlock) — profile search by nicknames on dozens of platforms.
- [AutOSINT](https://github.com/bharshbarger/AutOSINT) — automation of basic OSINT tasks.
- [snoop](https://github.com/snooppr/snoop) — scripts for analyzing social networks and metadata.

- [mosint](https://github.com/alpkeskin/mosint) — a utility for collecting information about emails/accounts/domains.

> **Tip:** Place your custom scripts in `tools/my-osint-scripts/` and add links to them in this file:
> ```markdown
> - [My scripts (examples)](./my-osint-scripts/)
> ```

---

## 📌 Notes and security
- When publishing case studies, **do not publish personal data** without consent — anonymize sensitive information.
- For private/paid services (Dehashed, IntelX, etc.), indicate if you used paid access.
- It is recommended to add a short instruction (README) to each folder with your own scripts.
- [datasploit](https://github.com/datasploit/datasploit) — a collection of modules for collecting data on objects (people, domain, IP). - [ReconDog](https://github.com/s0md3v/ReconDog) — a multi-purpose reconnaissance utility (supports multiple modules).
- [solana-mev-bot](https://github.com/i3visio/solana-mev-bot) — an example bot/script for blockchain analytics (Solana).
- [LHF](https://github.com/blindfuzzy/LHF) — a repository with tools/scripts (various tasks).
